Host-side gtest unit tests for crosspoint-reader.

Build and run:

  cmake -S test -B build/test
  cmake --build build/test
  ctest --test-dir build/test --output-on-failure -j

Run a single suite directly:

  cmake --build build/test --target StreamingJsonParserTest
  build/test/streaming_json_parser/StreamingJsonParserTest --gtest_filter='*'

Google Test is fetched via CMake FetchContent on first configure; the pinned
version lives in test/CMakeLists.txt.

Large synthetic dictionaries (on-device manual tests only):

  test/dictionaries/prep-all/ and test/dictionaries/prep-long/ are not checked
  in. Generate them before on-device preprocessing tests:

    python3 test/data/generate_dictionaries.py test/data/dictionary-sources/prep-all.json
    python3 test/data/generate_dictionaries.py test/data/dictionary-sources/prep-long.json

  Or regenerate all test dictionaries at once:

    python3 test/data/generate_dictionaries.py --all
